net.hudup.listener

Class AbstractDelegator

  • java.lang.Object
    • net.hudup.core.client.ProtocolImpl
      • net.hudup.listener.AbstractDelegator
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.lang.Runnable, Protocol, Runner
    Direct Known Subclasses:
    Delegator

    public abstract class AbstractDelegator
extends ProtocolImpl
implements Runner
    This is abstract class of delegator. Delegator is responsible for handling and processing user request represented by Request. Each time Listener receives a user request, it creates a respective delegator and passes such request to delegator. After that delegator processes and dispatches the request to the proper binding server. The result of recommendation process from server, represented by Response, is sent back to users/applications by delegator. In fact, delegator interacts directly with server. However, delegator is a part of Listener and the client-server interaction is always ensured.
    Version:
    10.0
    Author:
    Loc Nguyen
